Step 1: Initialize Git Repository:--
# Navigate to project directory
cd student-record-management-system

# Initialize git
git init

# Add all files
git add .

# Initial commit
git commit -m "Initial commit: Complete Student Record Management System"

Step 2: Create GitHub Repository:--

Go to https://github.com/new
Repository name: student-record-management-system
Description: "Full-stack Student Record Management System with Java Spring Boot, MySQL, and AWS"
Choose Public or Private
Don't initialize with README (we already have one)
Click "Create repository"

Step 3: Push to GitHub :--
# Add remote origin (replace YOUR_USERNAME)
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/student-record-management-system.git

# Push to main branch
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

Step 4: Set up GitHub Secrets (for CI/CD):--
Go to: Repository → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
Add these secrets:

AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
DB_PASSWORD
JWT_SECRET
